# Download GCC to work with C++ language

Link: https://winlibs.com/#download-release

Instructions:

1) The downloaded archive should be placed in the root of the C:// drive.

2) you need to copy the path to the bin folder (if you have done the upper step, it is: C:\mingw64\bin).

3) Go into your PC's environment variables and add this path to PATH

4) Run CMD and write "gcc --version" should show the version of your MinGW, if it doesn't, repeat step 3.
